hopobject.body: good material thanks eris-pharma.com Federal agencies are usually mostly closed on weekends, so the government shutdown will be less noticeable in the marble halls of Washington today. But the Capitol building will be unusually busy as lawmakers continue to huddle, looking for solutions to the shutdown and looming debt limit. And while some states have figured out how to reopen national parks, many museums and other tourist attractions will remain locked. Here are five things to know about the government shutdown Saturday (Day 12.)
